fll-installer (0.9.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * don't write /etc/kernel-img.conf anymore, it's usage is deprecated and
    discouraged.
  * allow grub-pc | grub-efi as alternative dependency for fll-installer.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 05 Jul 2011 03:19:25 +0200

fll-installer (0.9.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * depend on base-files (>= 6.4), we need it for /run/ (this implicitly
    ensures a new enough initscripts package as well).
  * clarify previously log message about missing procfs a bit.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 29 May 2011 04:12:06 +0200

fll-installer (0.9.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * add /run/ to the list of virtual filesystems to be bind-{,u}mounted as
    needed.
  * don't try to mount procfs on the host from within the installer, we
    have bigger problems if /proc isn't accessible on the host.
  * avoid $BOOTMANAGER_PROC trickery, the virtual filesystems are needed for
    all steps during the bootloader configuration.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 29 May 2011 02:56:14 +0200

fll-installer (0.9.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * bump standards version to 3.9.2, no changes necessary.
  * add /run/ to rsync exclusion list.
  * fix dangling eMail addresses.

