  * system_services.bm:
    - Change SERVICE_WHITELIST 'sed'ing to a more efficient way.
  * Define UID by id -ur if not yet defined and use UID afterwards.
  * Change #!/bin/bash to #!/bin/sh.

 -- Michael Deelwater <michael.deelwater@googlemail.com>  Sun, 16 Nov 2008 17:19:36 +0100

fll-installer (0.4.24) unstable; urgency=low

  * POSIX shell, Part III:
    - Remove bash array constructs in system_services.bm.
    - More quoting.
  * fix_usb_install.bm:
    - Always define device_map.

 -- Michael Deelwater <michael.deelwater@googlemail.com>  Sun, 16 Nov 2008 01:47:30 +0100

fll-installer (0.4.23) unstable; urgency=low

  * add Michael Deelwater <michael.deelwater@googlemail.com> to Uploaders.
  * remove no longer required breaks.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Fri, 14 Nov 2008 23:43:27 +0100

fll-installer (0.4.22) unstable; urgency=low

  * On the way to POSIX shell, Part II:
    - Remove files modules/common/check_params.bm and
      add_and_register_vars.bm. Their functions are never used anymore.
    - Remove all $" strings for formatting. There are no translations, yet.
    - Use printf instead of echo -e and $".
    - Make some bash arrays normal list of strings. system_services.bm is
      still in bash form.
    - Replace (( )) constructs.
    - Minor clean-up and quoting.

 -- Michael Deelwater <michael.deelwater@googlemail.com>  Fri, 14 Nov 2008 04:15:59 +0100

fll-installer (0.4.21) unstable; urgency=low

  * On the way to POSIX shell. Remove many bashisms and deprecated bash
    constructs, and clean up the code to look more consistent. This is a bunch
    of rather trivial changes that should not break anything.
    - Remove "function" declarations for functions.
    - Replace "source" by ".".
    - Replace $[ by $((.
    - Replace all [[ ]] by [ ] with correct quoting.
    - Remove all -a and -o test constructs.
    - Replace $UID by $(id -ur).
    - Replace substring expansion by #??? stripping.
    - Replace $(<file) by $(cat file).
    - Always use [ ] for test.

 -- Michael Deelwater <michael.deelwater@googlemail.com>  Thu, 13 Nov 2008 04:54:01 +0100

fll-installer (0.4.20) unstable; urgency=low

  * No need to change owner of files under the home. Everything that we copy
    into there gets the default uid/gid. Probably this is also what causes
    troubles when user wants to install over an existing home ( even though
    we do no recommend it)

 -- Joaquim Boura <x-un-i@berlios.de>  Sat, 08 Nov 2008 12:43:39 +0100

