fll-installer (0.4.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * a few more adaptions for initial (no-tweaked) grub2 compatibility.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Mon, 07 Jul 2008 15:39:45 +0200

fll-installer (0.4.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * remove bogus device.map/ kernel_vers exports.
  * proper quoting.
  * sed can do the same as perl.
  * bindmounts are already set up externally.
  * don't hide grub-install/ update-grub output.
  * remove duplicate proc mounting again.
  * only save the first 446 byte of a block device, we only want the MBR and
    not clobber the partition table on restore.
  * fix sed calls and make regexp more robust.
  * fix test for grub-gfxboot.
  * stop groot and root mangling, new update-grub detects UUIDs on its own.
  * clean-up.
  * refactor grub charset.
  * merge sed calls.
  * not perfect or even tested in all possible combinations, but good enough
    to get started and polish it until Ωυρέα.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Mon, 07 Jul 2008 01:20:03 +0200

