fll-installer (0.2.17) unstable; urgency=low

  * modules/backend/system_services.bm:
    - don't check that first argument returned by fll_analyze_initscripts is
    update-rc.d, just check it was returned. The system may be using insserv.
  * if you have a .sidconf in /root dir then calling fll-installer will do
    a partially silent installation. There are some options [-d|--debug] will
    output  the commands called in /tmp/.install.debug. The fifo used for
    the progressbar can be passed using [-i|--inotify <filename>] or using the
    old way: installer inotify_fifo. An -h option is also provided
    Errors ( not yet all are logged in the file /tmp/.installer.error
    Verbosity should/will be enhanced
    remove encrypted passwords from the config file

 -- Joaquim Boura <x-un-i@berlios.de>  Wed, 05 Mar 2008 00:14:28 +0100

